15:46.179 --> 15:48.748
Oh. Okay.
Ah.

15:48.848 --> 15:51.451
I see this neighborhood
rubbing off on you.

15:51.551 --> 15:53.853
(all exclaiming)

15:53.953 --> 15:56.656
That was delicious
as always, Mama.

15:56.756 --> 15:58.458
Oh, thank you, baby.
Where's your brother?

15:58.558 --> 16:01.561
Oh, I saw him on the side yard
eating a plate of fish.

16:01.661 --> 16:04.631
Wait a minute. My fish?

16:04.731 --> 16:06.233
Yeah. (laughs)

16:06.333 --> 16:07.900
Got 'em!

16:08.735 --> 16:11.138
Oh, no, no, no.
No, no, Mama, Mama.

16:11.238 --> 16:13.940
Please don't tell Marty
that I told you, okay?

16:14.041 --> 16:15.908
(sighs)
Don't you worry, baby.

16:16.009 --> 16:18.378
Oh, thank you. (chuckles)
I ain't no snitch.

16:25.252 --> 16:26.319
Aha!

16:26.419 --> 16:27.754
Oh, Mommy!

16:30.723 --> 16:32.592
This warms my heart.

16:32.692 --> 16:35.562
Mama, I tried. I tried
to be strong for Necie,

16:35.662 --> 16:37.830
but your fish kept calling me.

16:38.731 --> 16:40.900
I lied to the woman I love.
I am so ashamed.

16:41.000 --> 16:44.071
Oh, no, no, don't be,
sweetie. Don't be.

16:44.171 --> 16:47.974
Look, let me tell you
a secret about marriage.

16:48.075 --> 16:51.878
The occasional little
innocent lie never hurts.

16:51.978 --> 16:53.680
Really?
Sure.

16:53.780 --> 16:55.682
Like, your father
always lies and says

16:55.782 --> 16:57.850
that he doesn't
smoke cigars anymore,

16:57.950 --> 16:59.852
and I lie and say,

16:59.952 --> 17:04.257
"You've seen this dress
before." See?

17:04.357 --> 17:07.927
Okay, so, as far as anyone
knows, I didn't eat this fish?

17:08.027 --> 17:09.529
Marty, I'm your mother.

17:09.629 --> 17:11.264
I've always got your back.

17:11.931 --> 17:13.400
I didn't see you eat any fish.

17:13.500 --> 17:14.834
Hmm.

17:18.838 --> 17:21.007
Ah, what do you think
you're doing?

17:21.108 --> 17:22.875
It's just going
to go to waste!

17:22.975 --> 17:24.877
Listen, you may be
almost a teenager,

17:24.977 --> 17:27.447
but there are still consequences
for breaking my rules.

17:27.547 --> 17:29.549
There will be no video games,

17:29.649 --> 17:31.918
you are cleaning all of this up,

17:32.018 --> 17:35.021
and you are certainly
not getting ice cream.

17:35.122 --> 17:37.557
(sighs)
Sorry, Mom. I just...

17:37.657 --> 17:40.160
Austin thought it would be
cool to ride scooters,

17:40.260 --> 17:42.595
and I didn't want to be uncool.

17:42.695 --> 17:45.098
I didn't know what to do.

17:46.065 --> 17:48.568
It's okay, honey. I understand.

17:48.668 --> 17:50.137
Peer pressure can be hard,

17:50.237 --> 17:52.572
but it's only going
to get harder.

17:52.672 --> 17:55.342
But I know you're a good kid.

17:55.442 --> 17:58.478
Maybe next weekend we can go
see the Annie movie?

17:59.979 --> 18:02.215
(clicks tongue)
Do you want your ice cream back?

18:02.315 --> 18:04.651
Yes.
Well, you're not
getting it, liar.

18:04.751 --> 18:07.320
I am never going
to see that movie!

18:07.420 --> 18:12.091
Oh, yes, you are, and we are
gonna wear matching outfits!

18:16.463 --> 18:18.198
I don't understand
what's taking so long.

18:18.298 --> 18:20.400
Hey, Malcolm,
have you seen Thad?

18:22.402 --> 18:24.003
Nice try, Dave.

18:25.738 --> 18:27.440
You are not
getting me again.

18:27.540 --> 18:29.509
(fight bell clangs on TV)

18:29.609 --> 18:31.778
MAN (over TV):
It's the 12th round,
and these guys are toe to toe.

18:31.878 --> 18:34.147
I can't believe this.

18:34.247 --> 18:36.015
We're stuck waiting for power,

18:36.115 --> 18:38.685
and this guy is sitting there
watching my TV.

18:38.785 --> 18:40.620
Thad!

18:40.720 --> 18:43.456
These juice-hungry hordes
are sucking my power dry!

18:43.556 --> 18:46.092
Now, I need you
to get up there...
Dave, Dave, Dave, Dave, Dave.

18:46.193 --> 18:49.229
Chill out, man. I told him
he can take a breather.

18:49.329 --> 18:52.064
Calvin, it has been hours,
and we still have no power.

18:52.165 --> 18:54.867
I know, but look around, man.

18:54.967 --> 18:56.869
I mean, the spirit
that I'm feeling here--

18:56.969 --> 18:58.104
I haven't felt that

18:58.205 --> 19:00.273
in this neighborhood
in a long time.

19:00.373 --> 19:03.910
I mean, people are actually
enjoying each other's company.

19:04.010 --> 19:06.979
And... and Tuyen--
she invited me

19:07.079 --> 19:08.948
to her mah-jongg club.

19:10.917 --> 19:14.086
I mean,
it's like spades, but Asian.

19:14.187 --> 19:17.924
So, if this is what
getting off the grid gets you,

19:18.024 --> 19:20.793
then, I'm not
in a hurry to get back on.

19:20.893 --> 19:22.795
It is kind of nice

19:22.895 --> 19:24.431
seeing everybody out
like this, isn't it?

19:24.531 --> 19:26.165
Yeah, man.

19:26.266 --> 19:28.235
So why don't you just
sit back and relax?

19:28.335 --> 19:32.038
Have you some pho, man.
Get some pho.

19:32.839 --> 19:35.475
I'm down to pho.

19:35.575 --> 19:39.679
This is an excellent party,
Calvin.

19:39.779 --> 19:40.947
Well, it is, isn't it?

19:41.047 --> 19:42.782
I'm sorry about this morning.

19:42.882 --> 19:45.685
I'm Sherri, this is Andrea, and
we just moved in on Cresthaven.

19:45.785 --> 19:47.320
Oh, uh, nice to meet you.

19:47.420 --> 19:50.357
And we're still looking for
recommendations of a landscaper.

19:50.457 --> 19:53.693
All right, well, uh,
I'll see what I can do.

19:53.793 --> 19:55.395
Welcome to the neighborhood.

19:56.396 --> 19:57.764
Good morning!

19:57.864 --> 19:59.466
It is 9:30.

19:59.566 --> 20:01.301
Do you not see the moon?

20:11.077 --> 20:12.379
You know, that was fun.
Mm.

20:12.479 --> 20:14.781
Who would have thought
it would take a power outage

20:14.881 --> 20:16.616
to restore my faith
in this neighborhood?

20:16.716 --> 20:19.218
Hmm. Yeah, it was
a great night.

20:19.319 --> 20:23.323
You know, with the candlelight
and you next to me,

20:23.423 --> 20:25.592
it could become
an even better night.

20:25.692 --> 20:27.594
Oh, really?
Mm-hmm.

20:27.694 --> 20:29.829
So, are you trying
to do a little something?

20:29.929 --> 20:31.298
You know I am.
(power clicks on, beep)

